{
  "title": "Plan Your Disney Day",
  "date": "2026-07-04",
  "category": "Disney Experiment",
  "published": true,
  "excerpt": "A Disney itinerary intake form built around feeling, constraints, pacing, group dynamics, and what would genuinely make the day work.",
  "body": [
    "Some Disney plans start with a list of rides. This one starts with what kind of day you are trying to create.",
    "\n<div class=\"disney-callout\"><strong>Plan Your Disney Day</strong> \u00b7 This form is designed around what actually matters to your group, not just a list of attractions.</div>\n<form class=\"disney-form\" id=\"disneyPlannerForm\">\n  <div class=\"form-section\">\n    <div class=\"section-label\">Your Trip</div>\n    <div class=\"field\">\n      <label>Which park or parks?</label>\n      <div class=\"park-grid\">\n        <label><input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"park\" value=\"Magic Kingdom\"> Magic Kingdom</label>\n        <label><input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"park\" value=\"EPCOT\"> EPCOT</label>\n        <label><input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"park\" value=\"Hollywood Studios\"> Hollywood Studios</label>\n        <label><input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"park\" value=\"Animal Kingdom\"> Animal Kingdom</label>\n        <label><input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"park\" value=\"Disneyland\"> Disneyland</label>\n        <label><input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"park\" value=\"Disney California Adventure\"> Disney California Adventure</label>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"field\">\n      <label for=\"travel_dates\">When are you going?</label>\n      <p class=\"hint\">Month and approximate dates help account for crowds, seasonal events, and what is actually running.</p>\n      <input type=\"text\" id=\"travel_dates\" name=\"travel_dates\" placeholder=\"e.g. October 15\u201318, or early July\">\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"field\">\n      <label for=\"days\">How many days in the park?</label>\n      <input type=\"text\" id=\"days\" name=\"days\" placeholder=\"e.g. 2\">\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"field\">\n      <label for=\"group_composition\">Who is coming?</label>\n      <p class=\"hint\">Include ages for children. It helps make the plan realistic.</p>\n      <textarea id=\"group_composition\" name=\"group_composition\" placeholder=\"e.g. Two adults, one 6-year-old, one 3-year-old\"></textarea>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"field\">\n      <label>How familiar is your group with this park?</label>\n      <div class=\"radio-group\">\n        <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"experience\" value=\"First visit\"> First visit</label>\n        <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"experience\" value=\"A few visits\"> We have been a few times</label>\n        <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"experience\" value=\"Experienced\"> We know it well</label>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"form-section\">\n    <div class=\"section-label\">What This Day Is For</div>\n\n    <div class=\"field\">\n      <label for=\"feeling\">What feeling are you hoping to create?</label>\n      <p class=\"hint\">One sentence is enough. Examples: \u201cMy daughter wants to feel like a princess for a day\u201d / \u201cI want to cover as much as possible\u201d / \u201cWe want to slow down and actually enjoy it.\u201d</p>\n      <textarea id=\"feeling\" name=\"feeling\" placeholder=\"Describe the kind of day you are hoping for\"></textarea>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"field\">\n      <label for=\"non_negotiable\">Is there one thing that absolutely has to happen?</label>\n      <p class=\"hint\">A ride, character meeting, meal, or experience. If skipping it would genuinely disappoint someone, put it here.</p>\n      <textarea id=\"non_negotiable\" name=\"non_negotiable\" placeholder=\"e.g. My daughter needs to meet Ariel. This is the whole reason we are here.\"></textarea>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <button type=\"button\" class=\"accordion-trigger\" id=\"advancedToggle\">\n    <span>Help us understand how your day needs to work.</span>\n    <span class=\"arrow\">\u25bc</span>\n  </button>\n\n  <div class=\"accordion-content\" id=\"advancedContent\">\n    <div class=\"field\">\n      <label for=\"sensory\">Does anyone in your group have sensory sensitivities?</label>\n      <p class=\"hint\">Loud sounds, sudden motion, physical restraint, crowds \u2014 anything worth knowing.</p>\n      <textarea id=\"sensory\" name=\"sensory\" placeholder=\"e.g. Our youngest gets overwhelmed by loud announcements in enclosed spaces\"></textarea>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"field\">\n      <label>Are there young children who may struggle with transitions?</label>\n      <p class=\"hint\">Helps build smoother pacing and fewer abrupt changes between activities.</p>\n      <div class=\"radio-group\">\n        <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"transitions\" value=\"Yes\"> Yes, transitions are hard</label>\n        <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"transitions\" value=\"Sometimes\"> Sometimes, depends on energy levels</label>\n        <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"transitions\" value=\"No\"> Not really</label>\n        <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"transitions\" value=\"N/A\"> No young children in our group</label>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"field\">\n      <label>Do you want meal and snack breaks built into the schedule?</label>\n      <div class=\"radio-group\">\n        <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"meals\" value=\"Frequent\"> Yes, regularly \u2014 especially with young kids</label>\n        <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"meals\" value=\"Meals only\"> Just main meals</label>\n        <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"meals\" value=\"Flexible\"> We will figure it out as we go</label>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"field\">\n      <label for=\"unspoken\">Is there anything that would genuinely disappoint someone if it did not happen?</label>\n      <p class=\"hint\">Different from the non-negotiable above \u2014 this is the thing someone has not said out loud but would feel.</p>\n      <textarea id=\"unspoken\" name=\"unspoken\" placeholder=\"e.g. My mom has never been to Disney and will not say so, but seeing the castle at night would mean everything to her\"></textarea>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"field\">\n      <label for=\"other\">Anything else we should know?</label>\n      <textarea id=\"other\" name=\"other\" placeholder=\"Mobility considerations, dietary needs, group dynamics, anything that shapes how your day needs to work\"></textarea>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"submit-section\">\n    <button type=\"submit\" class=\"button primary\">Send My Request</button>\n    <p class=\"submit-note\">This opens an email with your answers. You can review before sending.</p>\n    <div class=\"form-confirmation\" id=\"formConfirmation\">Your email app should open with the itinerary request filled in.</div>\n  </div>\n</form>\n\n<script>\n(function () {\n  const trigger = document.getElementById('advancedToggle');\n  const content = document.getElementById('advancedContent');\n  const form = document.getElementById('disneyPlannerForm');\n  const confirmation = document.getElementById('formConfirmation');\n\n  if (trigger && content) {\n    trigger.addEventListener('click', function() {\n      const isOpen = content.classList.contains('open');\n      content.classList.toggle('open', !isOpen);\n      trigger.classList.toggle('open', !isOpen);\n      if (!isOpen && window.jzTrackEvent) {\n        window.jzTrackEvent('disney_advanced_open', { page_path: window.location.pathname });\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  if (form) {\n    form.addEventListener('submit', function(e) {\n      e.preventDefault();\n\n      const data = new FormData(form);\n      const parks = data.getAll('park').join(', ');\n      const lines = [\n        'Disney itinerary request',\n        '',\n        'Parks: ' + parks,\n        'Dates: ' + (data.get('travel_dates') || ''),\n        'Days: ' + (data.get('days') || ''),\n        'Group: ' + (data.get('group_composition') || ''),\n        'Experience: ' + (data.get('experience') || ''),\n        '',\n        'Feeling they want to create:',\n        data.get('feeling') || '',\n        '',\n        'Non-negotiable:',\n        data.get('non_negotiable') || '',\n        '',\n        'Sensory considerations:',\n        data.get('sensory') || '',\n        '',\n        'Transitions:',\n        data.get('transitions') || '',\n        '',\n        'Meals/snacks:',\n        data.get('meals') || '',\n        '',\n        'Unspoken disappointment:',\n        data.get('unspoken') || '',\n        '',\n        'Other notes:',\n        data.get('other') || ''\n      ];\n\n      if (window.jzTrackEvent) {\n        window.jzTrackEvent('disney_request', { page_path: window.location.pathname });\n      }\n\n      if (confirmation) {\n        confirmation.classList.add('visible');\n      }\n\n      const subject = encodeURIComponent('Disney itinerary request');\n      const body = encodeURIComponent(lines.join('\\n'));\n      window.location.href = 'mailto:jwebdevmt@gmail.com?subject=' + subject + '&body=' + body;\n    });\n  }\n})();\n</script>\n"
  ]
}